hat?! The?!&quot; Farmer &quot;What was that? Sounds like a mountain falling.&quot; &quot;I will go and see what happened sounded like it was over by the old summon tower.&quot;<br>
<br>
 I run up avoiding the Boogey and past the old Roman Tomb with dust still settling but the Sprits of the Guards still stand as ever at their post. ~ Such dedication to service that they do not even know they are dead and should seek there rest. ~ As I get up the Summoning Tower I see a cloud of dust settling behind and what sky...... I should not be seeing sky that low.... ~ what has happened? A new pass thru the mountains? Could it be the lost pass? ~ I head over the hill and down into the new pass seeing how thin of a barrier truly had been build and from the looks of it from this side it was man made...... or at least made by some intelligent being.<br>
<br>
 I head down thru the pass into the canyons seeing the heard s of wild ponies running free. I stand watching a herd run, but they are moving with too much purpose something is after them..... I duck behind a hill just as I see a head coming over the hill. ~That head is to big they could not be that close. The color..... OH MY GOD..... It is some kind of stone giant ~ I wander deeper into the cannon seeing a whole village of these stone giants. Knowing when I am over matched I quickly turn around and head out. I head out the pass and head back down to the farm to help with the boogey problems.<br>
<br>
 Later that night I meet up with Shyl and agreed to help take out some boogies with me. I close my eyes and begin to chant and make the gestures. The earth around Shyl and me rises, forming a think protective coat around both of us.  Shyl picks up his drum and begins to sing a soft but compelling tone as he matches the beat with his drum. I feel the power flowing thru me my hair almost standing on end. I start to chant and gesture. A molehill grows and hardens with the inner heat as Lava Elementals form and with a nod head off to attack my targets. With a different set of gestures and chant the very air around me begins to freeze. Frost forms on my cloths as Ice elements form. With a nod they turn and begin to throw balls of ice and snow at the boogeies. This goes on for a few hours when suddenly I hear a yell behind me. I spin seeing Shyl running away as fast as he can a rooter hot on his heels. He starts a new beat on the drum and the cadence of his song changes as he suddenly takes off from the rooter.<br>
<br>
 I follow and see what going on. “Shyl you have not made friends with them yet?” Shyl “Friends? With them? Are you nuts? Those things are meaner then the things we are fighting!” “Hahahahahahahahahaha they are just like big puppies….” Pinches nose. “Really smelly dogs but hey. I will help you all you need to do is feed them a little boogey and they leave you alone.” So over the next few hours me and Shyl killing Boogies letting Shyl feed the rooters boogey parts slowly gaining their trust.<br>
